Boil a #pot of salted @water{to taste} for the rigatoni.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

When boiling, add the @dried rigatoni{180%g} and cook until softened, ~{12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander and pop back in the pot.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #pan over medium heat.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(chopped into small pieces). Clean the @mushrooms{250%g} with kitchen paper and cut them into quarters.

When the oil is hot, add the onion and fry for ~{1-2%mins}. Add the mushrooms and cook for ~{5-7%mins}, stirring occasionally.

Add the @green pesto{1%sachet} and @creme fraiche{125%g} and heat for ~{2-3%mins}, until slightly thickened.

Roughly chop the @parsley{5%g} stalks and leaves.

Add the drained pasta to the pan with the mushroom pesto mixture.

Toss to coat fully.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide the pasta between #bowls.

Garnish with @grated Italian style hard cheese{25%g} and chopped parsley.